						<summary>

						<p>Slab built into the ceiling of the <hi rend="italic">mukha-maṇḍapa</hi> of the Agastīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1646, Krōdhi, Jyēshta śu. 5,</hi> corresponding to 1724 A.D., May 16, Saturday.</p>						

						<p>It records the construction of a <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> to god Agastīśvara of Pālūru by Rāmireḍḍi, son of Venkaṭa of Vuppalūru. It also refers the construction of a <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> by Gōpālayya and Daṁbōju.</p>						

						</summary>
